  "subject": "Docs: Modernise docs configuration for Python 3.13",
  "commit_message": "Docs: Modernise docs configuration for Python 3.13\n\nReplace lfdocs-conf dependency with standalone conf.py to eliminate the\nupstream blockdiag/seqdiag/swaggerdoc/pkg_resources dependency chain.\nThe lfdocs-conf package imports sphinxcontrib-blockdiag which requires\npkg_resources, removed from setuptools>=82.\n\nChanges:\n- conf.py: Replace 'from docs_conf.conf import *' with standalone ONAP\n  configuration matching doc-best-practice reference; fix deprecated\n  add_stylesheet -> add_css_file for Sphinx 8.x; add RTD context\n  injection block\n- conf.yaml: Remove (no longer required without lfdocs-conf)\n- requirements-docs.txt: Remove lfdocs-conf and all blockdiag/seqdiag/\n  swaggerdoc/nwdiag/needs/bootstrap dependencies; add modern Sphinx and\n  sphinx-rtd-theme version bounds\n- tox.ini: Update whitelist_externals -> allowlist_externals for tox 4;\n  add upper-constraints and setuptools dep; add -W -q flags to\n  sphinx-build; add docs-linkcheck to envlist with proper deps\n- .readthedocs.yaml: Replace obsolete python 3.7 and build image latest\n  with os ubuntu-24.04 and python 3.13; remove formats htmlzip\n- ribbon.css: Fix max-width from none to 800px per doc-rules\n- index.rst: Add toctree with cia-casablanca-release-notes to fix\n  Sphinx -W warning about orphaned document\n\nIssue-ID: CIMAN-33\nChange-Id: I13565ab009fc3012df27c02d5a6a592c8a5c72ff\nSigned-off-by: Matthew Watkins <mwatkins@linuxfoundation.org>\n",
